						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2416844)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2416844">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/anqxyr" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(966960); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=966960&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252027" alt="anqxyr" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=966960)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/anqxyr" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(966960); return false;" >anqxyr</a></span> <span class="odate time_1449129493 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">03 Dec 2015 07:58</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2416844">
									

<p>Foundation Tomes and Complete Collection are the same thing, differently packaged. FT are 12 books, 500 skips in tomes 1-6 each, canons in 7-8, and tales in 9-12. CC is the same, but in one huge book. CC is easier to work with, but some reader software balks at files of such enormous size. So if CC doesn't open for you, takes too long to open, or you just want to read tales and nothing else for example, then Foundation Tomes are what you need.</p>
<p>Monthly Digest have all the new stuff that was posted that month. They're handy if you've been away from the site for some time, and want to catch up.</p>
<p>WL ebook is analogous to CC SCP ebook, because WL is so tiny and rarely updated in comparison that there's no point in making other versions.</p>

							</div>

								
					
